  rbind(read_csv("../model_code/results/pursuit_trueswell_results.csv")) %>%
  filter(phase == "learning")

trueswell_trajectory_might_pursuit <- trueswell_might_pursuit %>%
  group_by(
    exposure, model
  ) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_accuracy = mean(accuracy),
    error_min =  mean(accuracy)-sd(accuracy)/sqrt(200),
    error_max =  mean(accuracy)+sd(accuracy)/sqrt(200),
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'exposure'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
trueswell_trajectory_fubg <- tibble("exposure"=c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5),
                            "avg_accuracy"=c(0.201, 0.233, 0.26, 0.298, 0.333),
                            "error_min"=c(0.201, 0.233, 0.26, 0.298, 0.333),
                            "error_max"=c(0.201, 0.233, 0.26, 0.298, 0.333),
                            "model"=c("FUb", "FUb", "FUb", 
                                              "FUb", "FUb"))

trueswell_trajectory_exp <- tibble("exposure"=c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5),
                            "avg_accuracy"=c(0.178, 0.222, 0.272, 0.311, 0.333),
                            "error_min"=c(0.149, 0.191, 0.239, 0.277, 0.298),
                            "error_max"=c(0.206, 0.253, 0.305, 0.345, 0.369),
                            "model"=c("Human (reported)"))

trueswell_trajectory <- trueswell_trajectory_might_pursuit %>%
  rbind(trueswell_trajectory_fubg) %>%
  rbind(trueswell_trajectory_exp) %>%
  mutate(
    participant = factor(case_when(
      model == "pursuit" ~ "Pursuit",
      model == "might" ~ "MIGHT",
      model == "Human (reported)" ~ "Human\n(reported)",
      TRUE ~ model
    ), levels = c("Human\n(reported)", "MIGHT", "FUb", "Pursuit"))
  )

trueswell_trajectory_plot <- ggplot(filter(trueswell_trajectory
                                           # , model == "Human (reported)"
                                           ), 
                                  aes(x = exposure, y = avg_accuracy, 
                                      color=participant)) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = participant)) +
  geom_line(aes(linetype=participant)) +
  scale_linetype_manual(values=c("solid", "dashed", "dotted", "dotdash")) +
  scale_color_manual(values=
                      # col2grey(
                        c("#5f1c99", "#b2abd2", "#fbd863", "#e66101")
                        # )
                    ) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=error_min, ymax=error_max), width=0.2, show.legend=FALSE) +
  labs(
    y = "Accuracy at test",
    x = "Learning"
  ) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),
        axis.title=element_text(size=16,face="bold"),
        legend.title=element_text(size=16, face="bold"),

        legend.position = "bottom"
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous("Accuracy at test", limits = c(0, 1), breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.1)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept=0.2, linetype="dotted")

Hypothesis testing

trueswell_hyp_might_pursuit <- trueswell_might_pursuit %>%
  group_by(
    previous_correct, model
  ) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_accuracy = mean(accuracy),
    error_min =  mean(accuracy)-sd(accuracy)/sqrt(300),
    error_max =  mean(accuracy)+sd(accuracy)/sqrt(300),
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'previous_correct'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.
trueswell_hyp_fubg <- tibble("previous_correct"=c(0, 1),
                            "avg_accuracy"=c(0.282, 0.282),
                            "error_min"=c(0.282, 0.282),
                            "error_max"=c(0.282, 0.282),
                            "model"=c("FUb", "FUb"))

trueswell_hyp_exp <- tibble("previous_correct"=c(0, 1),
                            "avg_accuracy"=c(0.21,0.47),
                            "error_min"=c(0.21-0.13,0.47-0.13),
                            "error_max"=c(0.21+0.1, 0.47+0.15),
                            "model"=c("Human (reported)"))

trueswell_hyp_data <- trueswell_hyp_might_pursuit %>%
  rbind(trueswell_hyp_fubg) %>%
  rbind(trueswell_hyp_exp) %>%
  mutate(
    correctLast = factor(previous_correct),
    participant = factor(case_when(
      model == "pursuit" ~ "Pursuit",
      model == "might" ~ "MIGHT",
      model == "Human (reported)" ~ "Human\n(reported)",
      TRUE ~ model
    ), levels = c("Human\n(reported)", "MIGHT", "FUb", "Pursuit"))
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(correctLast))

 trueswell_hyp_plot <- ggplot(trueswell_hyp_data, aes(x = correctLast,

  scale_pattern_manual(values=c("wave", "stripe", "stripe", "stripe", "stripe")) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=error_min, ymax=error_max), width=0.2) +

    y = "Accuracy at test",
    x = "Previous selection accuracy"

yy_might_pursuit <- read_csv("../model_code/results/might_9_yurovsky_results.csv") %>%
rbind(read_csv("../model_code/results/pursuit_yurovsky_results.csv")) %>%
filter(phase=="testing") %>%
mutate(
  experiment = substr(condition, 4, 4),
  condition = substr(condition, 6, nchar(condition)),
  word_type = case_when(
    trial_index < 7 ~ "homophone",
    TRUE ~ "singleton"
  ),
  referent = case_when(
    word_type == "singleton" ~ "singleton",
    word_type == "homophone" & accuracy == 1 & substr(selection, 2, 2) == 1 ~ "first meaning",
    word_type == "homophone" & accuracy == 1 & substr(selection, 2, 2) == 2 ~ "second meaning",
    TRUE ~ "incorrect"
  )
) %>%
filter(accuracy == 1) %>%
select(!accuracy) %>%
  group_by(model, experiment, condition, word_type, referent, subject) %>%
  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(
    acc = count / 6
  ) %>%
  group_by(model, experiment, condition, word_type, referent) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_accuracy = mean(acc),
    stderr = sd(acc) / sqrt(300)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'model', 'experiment', 'condition', 'word_type'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
yy_data <- yy_exp %>%
  rbind(yy_fubg) %>%
  rbind(yy_might_pursuit) %>%
  mutate(
    condition_name = factor(condition, levels = c("primacy", "recency", "both")),
    condition = as.numeric(condition_name),
    referent = factor(referent, levels = c("first meaning", "second meaning", "singleton")),
    left = referent == "singleton",
    color = case_when(
      referent == "singleton" ~  "#e66101",
      referent == "first meaning" ~ "#5f1c99",
      referent == "second meaning" ~ "#b2abd2"
    ),
    minb = mean_accuracy - stderr,
    maxb = mean_accuracy + stderr,
    exp = factor(case_when(
      experiment == 1 ~ "Massed",
      experiment == 2 ~ "Interleaved"
    ), levels = c("Massed", "Interleaved")),
    model = factor(case_when(
      model == "exp" ~ "Human\n(reported)", 
      model == "pursuit" ~ "Pursuit",
      model == "might" ~ "MIGHT",
      model == "FUb" ~ "FUb",
      model == "FUb-fixed" ~ "FUb-fixed"
    ), levels = c("Human\n(reported)",  "MIGHT", "Pursuit", "FUb", "FUb-fixed")),
    participant = factor(case_when(
      model == "Human\n(reported)" ~ "Human",
      TRUE ~ "Model"
    )),
    split = factor(case_when(
      model == "Human\n(reported)" ~ "human",
      model %in% c("pursuit", "mbp") ~ "hyp.-testing",
      TRUE ~ "global assoc."
    ), levels = c("human", "hyp.-testing", "global assoc."))
  ) 

yy_confidence <- yy_data %>%
  select(!c(participant, split, stderr)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = model, values_from = c(mean_accuracy, minb, maxb)) %>%
  mutate(
    min = `minb_Human\n(reported)`,
    max = `maxb_Human\n(reported)`
  ) %>%
  select(!c(`minb_FUb`, `maxb_FUb`, `minb_FUb-fixed`, `maxb_FUb-fixed`, 
            minb_Pursuit, maxb_Pursuit, minb_MIGHT, maxb_MIGHT, 
            `minb_Human\n(reported)`, `maxb_Human\n(reported)`)) %>%
  mutate(
    FUb = mean_accuracy_FUb > min & mean_accuracy_FUb < max,
    FUb_f = `mean_accuracy_FUb-fixed` > min & `mean_accuracy_FUb-fixed` < max,
    MIGHT = mean_accuracy_MIGHT > min & mean_accuracy_MIGHT < max,
    Pursuit = mean_accuracy_Pursuit > min & mean_accuracy_Pursuit < max
  )

yy_plot <- ggplot(mapping = aes(x = condition, y = mean_accuracy, fill = color, pattern = participant)) +
    facet_grid(rows=vars(model), cols=vars(exp), scales = "free") +
    geom_col_pattern(
      data = filter(yy_data, left),
      width = .3,
      color = "white",
      position = position_nudge(x = -.3),
      pattern_alpha=0.2
    ) +
    scale_pattern_manual(values=c("wave", "stripe"), guide="none") +
    geom_errorbar(
      aes(ymin = minb, ymax = maxb),
      data = filter(yy_data, left),
      width = .1,
      position = position_nudge(x = -.3)
    ) +
    geom_col_pattern(
      data = filter(yy_data, !left),
      position = position_stack(reverse=TRUE),
      color = "white",
      width = .3,
    ) +
    geom_errorbar(
      aes(y = y, ymin = y - stderr, ymax = y + stderr),
      data = filter(yy_data, !left) %>%
        group_by(model, exp, condition) %>%
        mutate(y = accumulate(mean_accuracy, sum)),
      width = .1
    ) +
    labs(
      x = "Condition", y = NULL,
      fill = "Referent selected"
    ) +
    scale_fill_identity(guide="legend", 
                        labels = levels(yy_data$referent)) +
    scale_x_continuous(
      breaks = 1:3 - .15,
      labels = levels(yy_data$condition_name)
    ) +
    theme_classic(base_size = 16) +
    ylim(0, 1) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.25, linetype = "dashed")

Yu & Smith 2007

yu_smith_data <- read_csv("yu_smith_results.csv") %>%
  group_by(condition, model) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_accuracy = mean(accuracy),
    error_min =  max(0, mean(accuracy)-sd(accuracy)/sqrt(300)),
    error_max =  min(1, mean(accuracy)+sd(accuracy)/sqrt(300)),
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    condition = factor(case_when(
      condition == 2 ~ "2x2",
      condition == 3 ~ "3x3",
      condition == 4 ~ "4x4"
    )),
    learner = case_when(
      model == "mbp" ~ "MBP",
      model == "pursuit" ~ "Pursuit",
      model == "perf_pursuit" ~ "Pursuit\n(perfect)"
    )
  ) %>%
  select(!model)

suanda_might_pursuit <- read_csv("../model_code/results/might_suanda_results.csv") %>%
  mutate(`buffer size` = 7) %>%
  rbind(mutate(
    read_csv("../model_code/results/might_3_suanda_results.csv"), 
    `buffer size` = 3)
  ) %>%
  filter(
    phase == "testing"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    model = case_when(
      `buffer size` == 7 & model == "might" ~ "MIGHT\n(adult - 7)",
      `buffer size` == 3 & model == "might" ~ "MIGHT\n(child - 3)"
  )) %>%
  group_by(condition, model) %>%
  summarize(
    avg_accuracy = mean(accuracy),
    sd_accuracy = sd(accuracy),
    count = n()
  )

suanda_exp_fubg <- tibble("condition" = c("highcd", "medcd", "lowcd", 
                                "highcd", "medcd", "lowcd",
                                "highcd", "medcd", "lowcd"
                                ), 
                  "model" = c("Reported", "Reported", "Reported",
                              "FUb", "FUb", "FUb",
                              "FUb-fixed", "FUb-fixed", "FUb-fixed"
                              ),
                  "avg_accuracy" = c(0.48, 0.39, 0.34,
                                     0.48, 0.39, 0.34,
                                     0.432, 0.413, 0.377
                                     ),
                  "sd_accuracy" = c(0.21, 0.20, 0.18, 
                                    0,0,0,
                                    0,0,0
                                    ),
                  "count" = c(28, 28, 28, 
                              1,1,1,
                              1,1,1
                              )
                  )

suanda_data <- suanda_might_pursuit %>%
  rbind(suanda_exp_fubg) %>%
  mutate(
    condition = factor(condition, levels = c("highcd", "medcd", "lowcd")),
    condition_g = factor(
      case_when(
        condition == "highcd" ~ "High",
        condition == "medcd" ~ "Med",
        condition == "lowcd" ~ "Low"
      ), levels = c("High", "Med", "Low")
    ),
    model = factor(model, levels=c("Reported", "MIGHT\n(child - 3)", 
                                   "MIGHT\n(adult - 7)"
                                   , "FUb", "FUb-fixed"
                                   )),
    participant = factor(case_when(
      model == "Reported" ~ "Human",
      TRUE ~ "Model"
    )),
    error_min =  avg_accuracy-sd_accuracy/sqrt(count),
    error_max =  avg_accuracy+sd_accuracy/sqrt(count)
  ) %>%
  filter(
    # model != "FUb"
  ) 

suanda_plot <- ggplot(suanda_data, aes(x = condition_g, y = avg_accuracy, fill = condition_g)) +
  geom_col_pattern(aes(pattern = participant),
    position = "dodge"
  ) +
  scale_pattern_manual(values=c("wave", "stripe"), guide="none") +
  facet_grid(cols=vars(model)) +
  ylim(0, 1.0) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=error_min, ymax=error_max), width=0.2) +
  labs(
    y = "Accuracy at test",
    x = "Condition: Contextual Diversity",
    fill = "Condition"
  ) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),
        axis.title=element_text(size=16,face="bold"),
        legend.title=element_text(size=16, face="bold"),
        legend.text=element_text(size=14),
        title=element_text(size=18,face="bold"),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 14),
        legend.position = "bottom"
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(values=
                      # col2grey(
                        c(
                          "#b2abd2",
                          "#fbd863",
                          "#e66101")
                        # )
                    , guide = "none"
                    ) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0.25, linetype = "dashed")
